===Etymology===
{{etyl|xno}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|citezein|lang=fro}} (spelling altered by influence of {{term|denizen|lang=en}}), from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{term|citeain|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|citoyen|lang=fr}}), from {{term|cite||settlement (regardless of size), later meaning [[cathedral]] town|lang=fro}} (Modern French {{term|cité|lang=fr}}, English {{term|city|lang=en}}), from {{term|citet|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|civitas||citizenship, community of citizens|lang=la}}, from {{term|civis||townsman, citizen|lang=en}} (English {{term|civil|lang=en}}, {{term|civilian|lang=en}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|kei-|to lie, homestead|lang=en}}.

